title: A. My First Sorting Problem
statement:
You are given two integers $$$x$$$ and $$$y$$$.

Output two integers: the minimum of $$$x$$$ and $$$y$$$, followed by the maximum of $$$x$$$ and $$$y$$$.
inputSpecification:
The first line contains a single integer $$$t$$$ ($$$1 \leq t \leq 100$$$) — the number of test cases.

The only line of each test case contains two space-separated integers $$$x$$$ and $$$y$$$ ($$$0 \leq x, y \leq 9$$$).
outputSpecification: For each test case, output two integers: the minimum of $$$x$$$ and $$$y$$$, followed by the maximum of $$$x$$$ and $$$y$$$.

samples.input:
10
1 9
8 4
1 4
3 4

name: My First Sorting Problem
